# Component Patterns

## File Structure

Every component folder MUST contain all four files:

```
atoms/Button/
  Button.tsx          # Implementation
  Button.test.tsx     # Tests
  Button.stories.tsx  # Storybook
  index.ts            # Barrel exports
```

## Implementation Pattern

```tsx
import { type ButtonHTMLAttributes } from "react";
import { cn } from "@/lib/cn";

const variantStyles = {
  primary: "bg-gradient-accent text-white shadow-md hover:brightness-110",
  secondary: "bg-surface text-foreground border border-border",
} as const;

export type ButtonVariant = keyof typeof variantStyles;

export interface ButtonProps extends ButtonHTMLAttributes<HTMLButtonElement> {
  variant?: ButtonVariant;
  className?: string;
}

export function Button({ variant = "primary", className, children, ...props }: ButtonProps) {
  return (
    <button className={cn("base-styles", variantStyles[variant], className)} {...props}>
      {children}
    </button>
  );
}
```

## Barrel Export Pattern

```ts
// index.ts
export { Button } from "./Button";
export type { ButtonProps, ButtonVariant } from "./Button";
```

Layer-level barrels (`atoms/index.ts`) re-export ALL components and types from that layer.

## Composition Rules

| Layer | Imports from | Never imports from |
|-------|-------------|-------------------|
| Atoms | Nothing (standalone) | Molecules, Organisms, Templates |
| Molecules | Atoms | Organisms, Templates |
| Organisms | Atoms, Molecules | Templates |
| Templates | Atoms, Molecules, Organisms | — |

## Key Conventions

- Components are **dumb/presentational** — no `"use client"` unless handling browser events. No API calls.
- Always accept `className?: string` and merge via `cn()` on the root element.
- Use **named exports** only — never `export default`. Both `export function Name(...)` and `export const Name = forwardRef(...)` are acceptable named exports.
- Extend native HTML element attributes for atoms (`ButtonHTMLAttributes`, `InputHTMLAttributes`, etc.).
- Use `as const` for variant/size style maps and export the `keyof typeof` type.
- Components that need ref forwarding use `forwardRef`:

```tsx
export const Input = forwardRef<HTMLInputElement, InputProps>(
  ({ className, error, ...props }, ref) => (
    <input ref={ref} className={cn("base-styles", className)} {...props} />
  ),
);
Input.displayName = "Input";
```
